<seg id="1">Man set alight on doorstep 'in targeted attack'</seg>
<seg id="2">A man has been set alight on his doorstep in what police believe is a targeted attack.</seg>
<seg id="3">The 48-year-old was soaked in flammable liquid, believed to be petrol, before bursting into flames outside his home in Skelmersdale, West Lancashire.</seg>
<seg id="4">He is in hospital in a critical but stable condition after suffering serious burns.</seg>
<seg id="5">Police have launched an attempted murder inquiry after they were called to the man's house at about 1am on Thursday.</seg>
<seg id="6">Detective Chief Inspector Pauline Stables, leading the investigation, said: "This is a horrific incident which has left a man in a very poorly condition in hospital.</seg>
<seg id="7">"We are carrying out a number of enquiries to try to identify those responsible.</seg>
<seg id="8">"While we are trying to establish a motive for what has happened, we do believe that the incident was targeted and I would like to stress that I don't believe there is any threat to the wider community at this time.</seg>
<seg id="9">"Someone out there knows who has done this and I would urge them to come forward and speak to us.</seg>
<seg id="10">"Has a loved one come home acting suspiciously, smelling of smoke or petrol or with unexplained injuries?</seg>
<seg id="11">"We need to find the people responsible for this dreadful crime."</seg>
</p>
